#hm-note[
  *On Numerology 4–6:* The student need not engage these deeply this week. The
  instruction is a first exposure. The stability of 4 (the four elements in their
  structured form), the restless midpoint of 5 (the pivot between extremes), and
  the harmony of 6 (the conjunction, the balance of opposites) will be revisited
  and will mean far more after Month 10's cohobation work. Plant the seed now.

  *On student impatience signals:* The Week 4 assignment reveals which students
  have a difficult relationship with time and waiting. If a student writes a
  defensive or dismissive response ("I don't really feel impatient, I'm fine with
  waiting"), flag this for a gentle one-on-one check-in at the Q1 Gathering.
  Genuine ease with waiting is relatively rare among beginning students. Defensive
  ease is common — and it usually means the student is not actually attending to
  the preparation or the practice with sufficient honesty.
]
